        "id": 5140
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-02T03:40:24Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So this is actually a map from an ordered list of StructParent Keys (the index, to which some base is added to create the key) to the nodeIds which reference them. From these StructParent Keys the ParentTree is created.\n\nIt seems that different StructParent Keys which pointed to the same node would all be identical mappings.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 412,
        "startChar": 27,
        "endLine": 412,
        "endChar": 55
      },
      "revId": "02084f4915b745c369f98a29ab1097b8d53048cf",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "660f8002_8dfb0387",
        "filename": "src/pdf/SkPDFTag.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 412,
      "author": {
        "id": 6205
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-07T20:59:27Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "That\u0027s correct. In practice that would mean that somehow there were\ntwo annotations associated with the same node. In the case of Chrome,\nthat wouldn\u0027t happen because each link (annotation) would be associated\nwith a different DOM node. But even if it did, it\u0027d just mean there\u0027d\nbe two keys pointing to the same node, which I think would be okay.",
      "parentUuid": "3649aa2f_b6bb5898",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 412,
        "startChar": 27,
        "endLine": 412,
        "endChar": 55
      },
